## What I Learned
This lab helped me get comfortable with how a real Windows domain works.

Main things I took away:
- How important DNS is (seriously everything breaks without it)  
- How to manage users, groups, and permissions in Active Directory  
- How to troubleshoot common help desk issues step by step  
- How Group Policy actually applies (and how easy it is to mess up)  
- How file sharing and permissions work in a real environment  

Overall this was one of the most useful labs I’ve done so far. It gave me real experience with the kind of tasks I’d be doing in an entry-level IT/help desk role.

